	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The second way is doable. The Lua script (or whatever) would need to figure out the level, scroll position etc of the current emulator instance, and fetch corresponding player states from the server. But like you said, there can't be any interaction, so I don't know how much fun it really would be. Maybe with the ability to chat it could be more fun.<br /><br />I guess it would be kind of similar to this: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://sarien.net/">http://sarien.net/</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
