		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Tetris!: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LT1eiLiMWkk">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LT1eiLiMWkk</a><!-- m --><br /><br />But I think if you want to play an NES game online, you should go with an emulator that supports kailerra like <a href="http://www.jabosoft.com/categories/1" class="postlink">JNES</a><br /><br />You could then make up to a 4 play online game, at least. If you're relying on paint functions from LUA it's not very NES. It'd be better to just write a retro looking computer program. If you want the online stuff to work on NES you need custom hardware and everyone who wants to play needs it as well. Even with custom hardware, the 8 sprites per scanline/64 sprite limit doesn't do much for massively multiplayer.

		

		</td>
